PART 8 — Your Exact Mixed Example
Code
#include <stdio.h>#pragma pack(2)struct Normal1 {    char a;    int b;} __attribute__((packed));struct Normal2 {    char a;    int b;};int main() {    printf("Normal1 = %zu\n", sizeof(struct Normal1));    printf("Normal2 = %zu\n", sizeof(struct Normal2));}
Output
Normal1 = 5Normal2 = 6

Why?
Normal1
packed removes padding.
0 a1-4 bsize=5
Normal2
Still under pack(2).
0 a1 pad2-5 bsize=6

