PART 15 — When NOT to Use
normal application structsperformance-critical arraysfrequently accessed numeric members

PART 16 — Golden Rules
Rule 1
Use natural alignment by default.
Rule 2
Use packed only when exact byte layout required.
Rule 3
Prefer push/pop around pragma pack.
Rule 4
packed affects one type, pragma may affect many later types.

